        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-29T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-09-29T11:00:00-05:00" n="683" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d683">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.3516/9–2948: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kohler</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-09-29T19:00:00+03:00">September 29, 1948—7 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 30—12:50 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2187. Am following up with Foreign Office without result so far question Dairen
                    telegrams, none which yet received here (Embtel 2057 to Department September 20,
                    repeated Nanking 27, Shanghai 30, Dairen 18).</p>
                <p>Sent Department 2187. Department pass Nanking 33, Shanghai 31, Dairen 19.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kohler</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
